---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="About S2P2 and the blog motto: Structures • Semantics • Systems • Stuff."
	pubDate={new Date('May 27 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>I'm S2P2.</p>

	<p>
		This is a personal blog about healthcare, code, AI, and the messy middle — but not only
		those things.
	</p>

	<p>The motto of this blog is:</p>

	<p><strong>Structures • Semantics • Systems • Stuff</strong></p>

	<p>
		It is not a strict set of categories. It is more like a simplified version of how I tend
		to think.
	</p>

	<p>
		I often start with <strong>structures</strong>: the anatomy of a topic. The parts,
		components, building blocks, fundamentals, and static knowledge. What is this made of?
		What needs to be identified before anything else can be understood?
	</p>

	<p>
		Then come <strong>semantics</strong>: closer to the physiology of a topic. Not just what
		each part is, but what it does, what it represents, how it behaves in context, and how
		its meaning changes when connected to other parts.
	</p>

	<p>
		Then come <strong>systems</strong>: how the structures and semantics interact. How parts,
		meanings, functions, and content connect into workflows, produce behavior, expose
		constraints, and sometimes become something useful.
	</p>

	<p>And then there is <strong>stuff</strong>.</p>

	<p>
		Stuff is anything else I want to keep here: notes, experiments, games, movies, cats,
		fragments, small observations, unfinished thoughts, or whatever else feels worth putting
		on the blog.
	</p>

	<p>
		So this site is partly a technical blog, partly a notebook, partly a playground, and
		partly a place for miscellaneous things I like.
	</p>

	<p>
		It starts from healthcare, programming, data, and AI, but it does not have to stay inside
		those borders.
	</p>
</Layout>
